======================================================================
PART 5: H DISTRIBUTION — TILING vs ARC PERSPECTIVE
  Tiling model: only C(n-1,2) = m_tiling variables (not all C(n,2) arcs)
  Because the backbone arcs are fixed!
  Q: Does the tiling perspective give different Fourier structure?
======================================================================

  n=5: m_tiling=6 positions

  TILING-SPACE FOURIER SPECTRUM (m=6 variables):
    level 0: energy= 88.35%, 1 nonzero
    level 1: energy=  5.72%, 5 nonzero
    level 2: energy=  5.49%, 15 nonzero
    level 3: energy=  0.34%, 12 nonzero
    level 4: energy=  0.10%, 7 nonzero
    level 5: energy=  0.00%, 0 nonzero
    level 6: energy=  0.00%, 0 nonzero

  Compare arc-space (m=10): levels 0 (75.95%), 2 (22.78%), 4 (1.27%)
  Tiling-space has DIFFERENT Fourier structure because:
  - Fewer variables (6 vs 10)
  - Different basis (tiling positions vs arc indicators)
  - Backbone arcs are NOT free variables in tiling space

  Odd-level energy in tiling space: 6.0589%
  (In arc space: exactly 0% because H(T)=H(T^op))
  In tiling space: the T^op symmetry maps to DIFFERENT tiling,
  so the odd-level vanishing does NOT hold in tiling coordinates!

